  "texts": [
    "However, the model does struggle with accurately predicting the ridges of 'Elongate dendritic' and 'Papillate' morphotypes, resulting in less precise segmentation for these classes.",
    "Rehn et al. (2019) present a novel approach to fossil charcoal particle identification and classification using two CNNs: a modified U-Net for segmentation and a VGG16 network for classification.",
    "The U-Net architecture was adapted by reducing the number of convolutional and deconvolutional layers between up-sampling and down-sampling stages, which minimized computational overhead while maintaining high segmentation accuracy.",
    "The VGG network was employed for morphotype classification, leveraging TL from a pre-trained VGG16 model, with the first 25 layers frozen to avoid relearning basic features, which improved training efficiency.",
    "However, the study relied on clean datasets with minimal non-charcoal particles, and thus the model's accuracy may be more limited in more complex, real-world scenarios."
